List top issues in US Healthcare

  Lack of access to healthcare for certain segments of the population, such as low-income individuals and rural communities.
  High cost of healthcare and prescription drugs.
  Inadequate insurance coverage and rising out-of-pocket costs for consumers.
  Disparities in healthcare access and outcomes based on race, ethnicity, and socioeconomic status.
  Shortages of primary care physicians and other healthcare providers in some areas.
  Fragmented and inefficient delivery of healthcare services.
  Lack of coordination and continuity of care between different providers and settings.
  Chronic disease management and prevention.
  Aging population and the increase in demand for healthcare services.
  Government funding and budget constraints on healthcare programs such as Medicare and Medicaid.
